HOW TO INSTALL VIB TO YOUR HARDDISK


    If  you  want  to use the VIB from your harddisk, then you have do
    the following:

    1. Copy the  VIB drawer and the VIB.info files for example to your
       DH0: partition.

    2. Take a text editor and  add the following text to your harddisk
       s/startup-sequence:   

       Assign Virus:    DH0:VIB/Virus   (contains all the texts)
       Assign V-IFF:      DH0:VIB/V-IFF (contains all the demos)

    3. But if you have got  this Virus Info Base version from "The New
       Superkillers"  disk,  please remember that all files are packed
       on  this disk.  Of course you can decrunch all the files on the
       disk,  but a better solution will be to transfer all the packed
       files  to your harddisk together with the decrunch tools on our
       disk.


       If  you want to use VIB from "The New Superkillers" you have to
       copy the following files to your harddisk:

       AmigaGuide.library to Libs:
       Powerpacker.library to Libs:
       Explode.libray to Libs:
       Earlyexplode to C:

       And add this line to your startup-sequence: EarlyExplode >nil:



    4. VIB  have been succesful  tested with the following  Amigaguide
       library versions:

       34.11 (62.932 bytes)
       34.8  (62.996 bytes)

                                                            ELS 02-94

